1
00:00:02,679 --> 00:00:04,199
No, no! Don't do anything to me.

2
00:00:44,199 --> 00:00:47,880
Speaking of those two boys

3
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:50,039
Pakin and Pakinai.

4
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,639
Their lives

5
00:00:52,639 --> 00:00:55,679
were nowhere near
this glamorous.

6
00:00:56,159 --> 00:00:58,519
They were street kids.

7
00:00:59,239 --> 00:01:00,639
Sleeping wherever night fell.

8
00:01:02,079 --> 00:01:05,280
Having parents was
like having none at all.

9
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:09,400
Both their mother and father
were addicts.

10
00:01:10,039 --> 00:01:11,800
They did nothing all day.

11
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:13,280
After getting high

12
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,920
they would just beat their kids.

13
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:20,639
Until those two

14
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:22,320
couldn't take it anymore.

15
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:24,559
So one day,
they hopped on a train

16
00:01:25,039 --> 00:01:28,599
and ran away to Bangkok,
looking for a better life.

17
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:30,239
But little did they know

18
00:01:30,679 --> 00:01:31,960
that Bangkok

19
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:35,519
isn't a paradise for everyone.

20
00:01:35,519 --> 00:01:37,199
Every single day and night

21
00:01:37,199 --> 00:01:39,280
they had to fight

22
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:43,639
against the local thugs,
getting battered every day.

23
00:01:45,519 --> 00:01:47,360
Is that why

24
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:48,760
those two love each other

25
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:50,719
and have such a deep bond?

26
00:01:50,719 --> 00:01:52,079
Exactly.

27
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,039
It's not just ordinary love.

28
00:01:56,039 --> 00:01:58,960
They would literally die
for each other.

29
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:02,400
If one of them gets hurt

30
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,159
the other will gladly take the pain.

31
00:02:04,719 --> 00:02:07,800
And if one of them dies

32
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:08,920
Think about it.

33
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:12,519
Would the other one be
willing to die as well?

34
00:02:16,119 --> 00:02:17,159
Aunt Tammy.

35
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:19,559
You've said too much.

36
00:02:19,559 --> 00:02:20,920
Pakin/ Khun Pakin.

37
00:02:25,039 --> 00:02:26,559
No, no! Don't do anything to me.

38
00:02:26,559 --> 00:02:29,280
I didn't mean any harm.

39
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,480
I just wanted to know a bit more

40
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:33,000
about Pakinai and you,
Khun Pakin. That's all.

41
00:02:35,639 --> 00:02:36,719
About Pakinai?

42
00:02:37,679 --> 00:02:40,360
Do you still not know enough?

43
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:42,119
Of course you don't.

44
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,440
Because if you truly
knew my brother

45
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:46,599
you wouldn't have done
what you did to him.

46
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:48,440
I didn't do anything!

47
00:02:48,679 --> 00:02:49,079
Bullshit.

48
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,719
When are you going to
stop your bullshit?

49
00:02:51,719 --> 00:02:52,880
Saturn.

50
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:53,880
I'm not him.

51
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:58,320
You probably didn't know this

52
00:02:58,599 --> 00:03:00,360
but about you and Pakinai

53
00:03:01,119 --> 00:03:01,960
I knew everything.

54
00:03:02,119 --> 00:03:03,400
I've been watching
the whole time.

55
00:03:04,199 --> 00:03:05,880
Since the very first day
I heard your name

56
00:03:06,199 --> 00:03:07,639
do you know what I did?

57
00:03:08,199 --> 00:03:09,920
I dug into your past.

58
00:03:10,239 --> 00:03:11,599
Just to make sure

59
00:03:12,239 --> 00:03:13,719
that my brother
chose the right person.

60
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:19,039
P'Dao.

61
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,079
Why would you do this to me?

62
00:03:21,079 --> 00:03:22,760
What did i do wrong?

63
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,079
You still have the nerve to ask me

64
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:25,199
what you did wrong?

65
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:26,719
I should have slapped your face.

66
00:03:26,719 --> 00:03:27,840
You idiot.

67
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:30,159
What is the meaning of this?!

68
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:32,679
Look at this.

69
00:03:33,039 --> 00:03:33,360
Look!

70
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:35,559
Why do you have to
treat him like this?

71
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,000
I was just teaching Lookkai a lesson.

72
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,320
As an intern

73
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,679
he needs to know that
our hotel excels in service.

74
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,679
The customer's needs
must always come first.

75
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:43,519
But this

76
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,960
it's just a single glass of cocktail

77
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,079
and he couldn't even serve it right.

78
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:48,119
To me, this is a failure.

79
00:03:48,119 --> 00:03:49,639
Substandard.

80
00:03:49,639 --> 00:03:51,199
It was just a glass of water!

81
00:03:51,199 --> 00:03:52,840
If he made a mistake,
you could've just told him.

82
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:54,000
Aunt Khae.

83
00:03:54,239 --> 00:03:56,159
Are you getting too old to remember?

84
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,400
You were the one

85
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,159
who taught me this since I was a kid.

86
00:03:59,679 --> 00:04:00,920
That I must never
accept any mistakes

87
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:01,880
from the staff.

88
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:07,280
You're going too far, Saturn.

89
00:04:07,519 --> 00:04:08,920
Not at all.

90
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:11,039
Because this is my style
of management.

91
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:12,760
If anyone isn't satisfied

92
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:13,880
you're welcome to resign.

93
00:04:14,159 --> 00:04:16,360
Both mother and son can leave.

94
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:21,920
Once I saw your true colors

95
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:24,159
I made a vow

96
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:26,679
that I would never let my brother

97
00:04:27,519 --> 00:04:28,559
spend his life

98
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:31,159
with someone who acts like

99
00:04:31,159 --> 00:04:32,599
an absolute piece of trash like you.

100
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:33,960
But sadly

101
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:36,400
it was too late.

102
00:04:47,639 --> 00:04:49,119
Will you marry me?

103
00:04:49,119 --> 00:04:50,800
I promise

104
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,360
I will be the rings

105
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,960
that orbit Saturn forever.

106
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:56,119
For the rest of my life.

107
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:02,960
"Is that all you have to say?

108
00:05:07,159 --> 00:05:09,599
Will you marry me?

109
00:05:16,079 --> 00:05:16,920
Pakinai

110
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,320
You should know

111
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:20,880
that Saturn

112
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:23,400
already has its own bright rings.

113
00:05:24,519 --> 00:05:25,360
It doesn't need

114
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,639
them from anyone else.

115
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,239
Remember that.

116
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,159
Heartless.

117
00:05:46,159 --> 00:05:47,639
How many men

118
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:49,440
have been manipulated by P'Saturn?

119
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,519
Tricked into falling for him

120
00:05:50,519 --> 00:05:52,000
only to be tossed aside
so ruthlessly like this.

121
00:06:08,559 --> 00:06:09,920
You bastard!

122
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:10,840
Hey, Pakin.

123
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:13,320
That's enough.
He's battered enough for today.

124
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:14,039
Enough, enough.

125
00:06:14,039 --> 00:06:14,960
Let's go. Break it up.

126
00:06:16,199 --> 00:06:17,280
Give him a break.

127
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:20,559
He's going to be with
us for a long time, man.

128
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,559
Don't finish him off in one day.

129
00:06:22,559 --> 00:06:23,719
Stretch it out over many days.

130
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,480
Take your time with it.

131
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,639
Damn it!

132
00:06:26,679 --> 00:06:28,840
Yeah, let's go.

133
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,840
You should get some sleep now.

134
00:06:32,199 --> 00:06:33,280
Always asking for trouble.

135
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:35,119
Now you've dragged me into it too.

136
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,719
P'Mavin.

137
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:50,480
Calling me in for
questioning like this

138
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:52,400
do you suspect me of something?

139
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,159
Not at all.

140
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:55,760
Please, have a seat first.

141
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:58,519
I'm just calling everyone in

142
00:06:58,519 --> 00:06:59,679
for a chat.

143
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,679
Hoping to gather
some more information

144
00:07:02,159 --> 00:07:03,079
about where Khun Venus

145
00:07:03,079 --> 00:07:03,960
and Khun Saturn

146
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:05,639
were last seen.

147
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,599
Well, as everyone already knows

148
00:07:08,519 --> 00:07:09,760
That day, P'Saturn

149
00:07:10,039 --> 00:07:11,320
didn't show up at the hotel at all.

150
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:13,639
As for P'Venus

151
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:14,760
he was busy preparing for the event.

152
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:15,599
Because he wanted

153
00:07:15,599 --> 00:07:17,199
everything to be perfect

154
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,760
right up until the event started.

155
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:21,719
P'Dao

156
00:07:21,719 --> 00:07:22,920
I've asked everyone around.

157
00:07:23,199 --> 00:07:24,719
No one has seen P'Saturn.

158
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,039
Where could he be?

159
00:07:27,559 --> 00:07:29,880
I've called him a hundred times

160
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,320
but he's still not picking up.

161
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:32,440
I think

162
00:07:32,679 --> 00:07:33,480
P'Saturn

163
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,960
might just want to surprise us.

164
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,079
Waiting for all the guests to arrive

165
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:39,880
and then making a
grand entrance at the end.

166
00:07:40,599 --> 00:07:42,719
If that's the case, then great, Lookkai.

167
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,280
But right now,
I'm starting to get worried.

168
00:07:45,559 --> 00:07:46,239
What if

169
00:07:46,239 --> 00:07:47,519
something happened to Saturn?

170
00:07:47,719 --> 00:07:49,440
I think you should take a rest first.

171
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:50,840
Sit down here.

172
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:55,360
P'Dao

173
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,599
please don't stress out just yet.

174
00:07:57,519 --> 00:07:58,760
You've been working hard
since this morning.

175
00:08:00,679 --> 00:08:02,559
Sit down and have some
cold water first.

176
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,760
The guests will all be here soon.

177
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:08,679
Thank you.

178
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,520
Do you happen to know

179
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,600
which staff member

180
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,119
served water to Khun Venus?

181
00:08:20,239 --> 00:08:22,079
That staff member

182
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:24,239
was probably one of the temps

183
00:08:24,239 --> 00:08:26,439
we hired specifically for this event.

184
00:08:27,479 --> 00:08:28,199
I think

185
00:08:28,199 --> 00:08:29,560
it was their first time working here.

186
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:31,840
Could you check and see

187
00:08:32,319 --> 00:08:33,039
what that staff

188
00:08:33,359 --> 00:08:33,880
member's name is?

189
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:36,079
Sure.

190
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:38,119
I'll go ask

191
00:08:38,119 --> 00:08:40,399
the banquet manager.

192
00:08:42,239 --> 00:08:42,720
Alright

193
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:45,000
one last question.

194
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:46,920
After you

195
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,600
spoke with Khun Venus

196
00:08:49,239 --> 00:08:51,159
did you see him again?

197
00:08:52,279 --> 00:08:53,479
Not at all.

198
00:08:54,119 --> 00:08:56,760
I was too busy running
around sorting things out

199
00:08:57,199 --> 00:08:58,960
until the event started.

200
00:08:59,359 --> 00:09:00,119
That's when

201
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:02,880
I realized P'Venus had disappeared.
